author: Inside Edition
description: Nine-year-old Melodee Buzzard was last seen three weeks ago. Surveillance photos show Melodee at a car rental business wearing a hooded sweatshirt and detectives say a very large dark wig, perhaps to disguise her appearance. Police say Melodee's mother, Ashlee Buzzard, left Lompoc, California in a rented vehicle with the girl to Nebraska, then Kansas. The mom returned home making the 3,000-mile trip in three days. Cops say when Ashley came back, Melodee was nowhere to be found.
title: Where Is 9-Year-Old Melodee Buzzard?

author: Inside Edition
description: A speeding Porsche jumped a curb, slamming into a young man on a first date, then hitting a light pole. The driver, Kristina Chambers, claims her high heels got stuck on the pedals, and that's why she could not control the car. Inside Edition producer Lauren Lavelle gave it a try and it sure was a challenge. Chambers was found guilty of manslaughter and sentenced to 11 years and 14 days in prison.
title: Woman Sentenced After Blaming Her High Heels For Fatal Car Crash

author: Inside Edition
description: In a collaboration, CBS NEWS and INSIDE EDITION investigate the growing trend of endangered baby spider monkeys being trafficked, driven in part, experts say, by people showing them off on social media. INSIDE EDITION went undercover as a potential buyer, connecting with two baby spider monkey sellers advertising on TikTok before meeting them in person in Texas parking lots. INSIDE EDITION did not buy the babies. For CBS News' report, click this link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AJvldI68eK8
title: Inside Edition & CBS News Investigation Finds Spider Monkeys For Sale

author: Inside Edition
description: At a grocery store in North Nashville, shoppers say they're making some difficult choices. With the ongoing government shutdown, some of them worry about how they're going to buy food come November. WTVF reports 121,000 families in Middle Tennessee could lose their SNAP benefits, and according to one cashier at this store, the majority of customers use food assistance. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Tennessee Families Worry About SNAP Benefits Amid Government Shutdown

author: Inside Edition
description: Parts of the Caribbean are battening down and preparing for an historic weather event. Hurricane Melissa is a Category 5 storm, and the National Hurricane Center says its wind speeds reach up to 180 mph. As Melissa approaches Jamaica, people there are securing their homes and property. The storm is expected to be the most powerful to hit the island since weather records have been recorded – for 174 years.
title: Hurricane Melissa Is Most Powerful Storm To Hit Jamaica In At Least 174 Years

author: Inside Edition
description: Twenty-three-year-old Audrey Eckert beat out 50 other contestants to win the new Miss USA crown. However, the crowning ceremony is coming with a big heap of controversy.
title: Reigning Miss USA Alma Cooper Wasn't Present To Crown New Miss USA #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Tune in to Inside Edition today for a full-length segment, in collaboration with CBS News, investigating the growing trend of endangered baby spider monkeys being sold.
title: Preview: Investigation Finds Spider Monkeys For Sale

author: Inside Edition
description: Is this really the best time for a music break? This woman is in the middle of brain surgery. Actually, doctors say talking to a conscious patient is the best way to get feedback on whether they're getting the right part of the brain. Denise Bacon is the woman in this unusual situation. She's loved making music with a band, but Parkinson's Disease has prevented her from playing her beloved clarinet for the past five years. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Parkinson's Patient Plays Clarinet During Brain Surgery

author: Inside Edition
description: The good Samaritan nurses happened to be passing by, and came to the Kentucky trooper's aid. They applied a tourniquet using a belt, and tried to keep the injured officer conscious.
title: Mother-Daughter Nurses Save Wounded Trooper #shorts
